# 🧠 Productivity Dashboard

A Fully all-in-one **Productivity Dashboard** built with HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.  
It combines a **Todo List**, **Pomodoro Timer**, **Motivational Quotes**, **Daily Planner**, and **Goal Tracker** to help you stay organized and motivated throughout your day.

---

## 🚀 Features

### ✅ Todo List
- Add and delete personal tasks
- Track pending work in real-time

### 📅 Daily Planner
- Time-blocked planner from 9 AM to 5 PM
- Save tasks for each hour using localStorage
- User-friendly input fields and save buttons

### ⏱ Pomodoro Timer
- 25-minute timer with start/reset functionality
- Built-in productivity technique to boost focus
- Plays an alarm sound on completion

### 💡 Motivational Quotes
- Random quote displayed every page load
- Encourages positive mindset and consistency

### 🎯 Daily Goals Tracker
- Tick off up to 5 goals every day
- Simple checkbox UI to track personal progress

### 🕒 Live Clock & Date
- Displays the current day, date, and time
- Auto-updates every second

---

## 🧾 Project Structure

Productivity-Dashboard/
├── index.html # Main UI structure
├── style.css # All styles and responsiveness
└── script.js # Core logic for features (todo, timer, goals, etc.)

## 🛠️ Technologies Used

- **HTML5** – Semantic structure
- **CSS3** –  styling
- **JavaScript (ES6)** – DOM manipulation, events, localStorage, timers

---

## 💻 How to Run Locally

1. Clone the repo:

git clone https://github.com/mikierror/Productivity-Dashboard.git
Navigate into the folder:


cd Productivity-Dashboard
Open index.html in any browser:


open index.html
